# Backend Rules (Python 3.12 + FastAPI)

Defer to `backend/AGENTS.md` for layout and commands.

## Code style

- **`ruff` + `pyright` strict.** Run `make -C backend lint typecheck` before commit.
- Async-first. `async def` everywhere; never call sync I/O inside an async route.
- Use `structlog.get_logger(__name__)` — never `print`, never `logging.*`.
- Type-annotate every function. Prefer `from typing import Annotated` for FastAPI deps.
- Imports: stdlib, third-party, `app.*` — separated, sorted by ruff isort.

## FastAPI patterns

- Route signature: `(<path params>, body: <Schema>, current_user: CurrentUser, session: SessionDep) -> <ResponseSchema>`.
- Use the existing dependency aliases in `app/dependencies.py` (`SessionDep`, `CurrentUser`, `ChannelMemberDep`). Add new ones there, not inline.
- HTTPException with explicit `status_code=` and `detail=`. Never bare `raise`.
- Response models always declared via `response_model=`.

## Database

- One model per file under `models/`. SQLModel `table=True` for tables, no implicit relationships unless tested.
- UUID primary keys (`uuid.uuid4` default). `created_at`/`updated_at` on every table.
- Soft delete via `deleted_at` — never hard delete.
- New columns / tables require: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<purpose>"` + review the generated migration.
- Never edit a merged Alembic revision; add a new one.

## WebSocket

- All event types live in `schemas/ws.py` `WSMessageType` enum.
- Authenticate before `await ws.accept()`. Close with code `4001` on auth failure.
- Every event has a Pydantic payload schema. Validate before persisting.
- Publish via both `publish()` (Redis) and `manager.broadcast_to_channel()` until Epic 6 (`S6.1`) lands.

## Forbidden

- `print()` for logging.
- `time.sleep` in async code.
- `requests` / `httpx.Client` (sync). Use `httpx.AsyncClient`.
- Wildcard imports.
- Inline raw SQL except in migrations or read-only EXPLAIN scripts.
